WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.000
[Unknown]: IVM

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:35.440
[Amit Varma]: The grammar, the skills required, the incentives at play, as an economist would say, the kind

00:00:35.440 --> 00:00:39.240
[Amit Varma]: of youngsters who come into the game, the kind of people who watch it and the reasons

00:00:39.240 --> 00:00:44.380
[Amit Varma]: for which they watch it. Everything about cricket has changed. And in this time, everything

00:00:44.380 --> 00:00:50.280
[Amit Varma]: about India has also changed. More than 60% of the country today was born after the forced

00:00:50.280 --> 00:00:57.180
[Amit Varma]: economic liberalization of 1991. And the social and cultural changes have been vast. Equally,

00:00:57.180 --> 00:01:02.840
[Amit Varma]: in this time, technology has also taken quantum leaps. And the world in 2018 would seem a

00:01:02.840 --> 00:01:08.200
[Amit Varma]: science fiction world to the boy of 1991. How could cricket not change?

00:01:08.200 --> 00:01:17.120
[Unknown]: Welcome to the scene and the unseen, our weekly podcast on economics, politics and behavioral

00:01:17.120 --> 00:01:22.160
[Unknown]: science. Please welcome your host, Amit Badma.

00:01:22.160 --> 00:01:26.520
[Amit Varma]: Welcome to the scene in the unseen. My episode last week was called the evolution of everything

00:01:26.520 --> 00:01:31.760
[Amit Varma]: in which my brilliant guest Matt Ridley described how Charles Darwin and Adam Smith had the

00:01:31.760 --> 00:01:37.520
[Amit Varma]: same grand idea and how everything evolves in bottom up ways. We spoke about the universe,

00:01:37.520 --> 00:01:43.200
[Amit Varma]: about life, language, cities, economy and the sense of self in that context. Well, today's

00:01:43.200 --> 00:01:48.080
[Amit Varma]: episode is about the evolution of cricket. And my guest is someone who's been a hero

00:01:48.080 --> 00:01:53.000
[Amit Varma]: of mine for a couple of decades now. Harsha Bhogle is a legend of cricket commentary,

00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:57.880
[Amit Varma]: and he embodies a pleasant contradiction of being both a larger than life figure, as a

00:01:57.880 --> 00:02:02.760
[Amit Varma]: celebrity stature makes him, as well as being down to earth and humble. He showed great

00:02:02.760 --> 00:02:07.000
[Amit Varma]: kindness to me in my past life as a cricket journalist, which I suspect he may not even

00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:11.540
[Amit Varma]: remember. And I was delighted when he agreed to appear on the scene in the unseen to talk

00:02:11.540 --> 00:02:17.200
[Amit Varma]: about how cricket has evolved in the course of his nearly three decades in the game. But

00:02:17.200 --> 00:02:22.560
[Amit Varma]: before we cut to the conversation I had with him, let's take a quick commercial break.

